    category: "Common Truck and Trailer Repairs",
    excerpt: "Semi-trucks are the backbone of the transportation industry, but they are prone to several common issues that can affect their reliability and performance.",
    featuredImage: "https://cttruckshop.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/SemiTruck1800.jpg",
    metaDescription: "Learn about the most common semi truck problems including brake issues, oil leaks, electrical system failures, and how to address them.",
    content: "<h1>Common Semi Truck Problems</h1><img src=\"https://cttruckshop.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/DZ9_2832_11zon-1-e1675877387407.jpg\" alt=\"fleet-maintenance-and-repair\" /><h2>Semi Trucks Problems</h2><p>Semi-trucks are the backbone of the transportation industry, but they are prone to several common issues that can affect their reliability and performance. Here are some of the most prevalent semi-truck issues:</p><p>1. Brake issues: Brake problems are among the most critical safety concerns for semi-trucks. The heavy loads and constant braking during long-haul journeys can lead to brake wear and deterioration. Common brake issues include worn brake pads, malfunctioning brake calipers, and air brake system leaks.</p><p>2. Oil leaks: Oil leaks can occur in various components of a semi truck's engine and drivetrain. These leaks may stem from worn gaskets, damaged seals, or cracks in the engine block.</p><p>3. Electrical system issues: Modern semi-trucks rely heavily on intricate electrical systems to control various functions, including lighting, engine management, and safety features.</p><p>4. Tire problems: Tires are a critical component of any semi-truck, and issues like blowouts, tread separation, and uneven wear can be dangerous and costly.</p><p>5. Engine overheating: Semi-truck engines generate a significant amount of heat during operation. Overheating can result from coolant leaks, malfunctioning thermostats, or clogged radiators.</p><p>6. Transmission issues: The transmission is a vital part of any semi-truck, and problems can arise from worn-out clutch plates, damaged gears, or low transmission fluid levels.</p><p>In conclusion, while semi-trucks are built for heavy-duty tasks, they are not immune to common issues. Regular maintenance and prompt attention to any emerging problems are essential to keep these vehicles running safely and efficiently. At <a href=\"https://cttruckshop.com/\">CT Truck and Trailer Shop</a>, we specialize in diagnosing and repairing all types of semi-truck problems.</p>"
